==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peptohydrochloric
<hw>Pep`to*hy`dro*chlo"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Peptone</er>, and <er>Hydrochloric</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>Designating a hypothetical acid (called
<xex>peptohydrochloric acid</xex>, <xex>pepsinhydrochloric acid</xex>,
and <xex>chloropeptic</xex> acid) which is supposed to be formed when
pepsin and dilute (0.1-0.4 per cent) hydrochloric acid are mixed
together.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peptone</ent>⟦br⟧
